{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"gnaw-timer-mocha","description":"## Why\n\nBlocking is project-owned policy; rebar's job is to surface the same eval/calibration instruments\nit uses on its built-ins so a maintainer can decide informed. Today `eval_solver.run_case` is a\n**closed hardcoded dispatch** (only `completion-verifier` / `ticket-quality` / `spec-alignment`;\nraises otherwise) and the CLI is validate-only — so a project criterion cannot be run through the\neval harness at all.\n\n## What\n\n- A criterion-aware runner extending `eval_solver.run_case` so an arbitrary (built-in or project)\n  criterion prompt_id is runnable — reconcile the invocation model (the criterion runs as its\n  Pass-1 finder against a fixture); resolve the T3 advisory (the existing solver's invocation model\n  vs a per-criterion prompt).\n- `rebar criteria eval <id>` — a live CLI (not validate-only) that runs the criterion's\n  must-fire/must-not-fire + discrimination fixtures from `.rebar/evals/<id>.eval.yaml` (discovery\n  already exists) with N-run stability.\n- A calibration view over the existing κ/parity primitives: per criterion print **recall**\n  (=fraction of must-fire fixtures it fires on), **false-accept** (=fraction of must-not-fire it\n  wrongly fires on), **Cohen's κ** and **agreement %** (verdict vs the fixture's labeled expect).\n  Reconcile the preview/eval `verdict` vocabulary with the fixture `expect` vocabulary.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Files: `src/rebar/llm/eval_solver.py` (criterion-aware dispatch), `src/rebar/llm/eval.py` /\n  `eval_scorers.py` (reuse discrimination scorers, κ, parity), `src/rebar/_cli/_llm_commands.py`\n  (`rebar criteria eval`), calibration rendering.\n- Depends on story `#1` (a criterion must be loadable/activatable to eval it).\n- Out: REVIEW_RESULT FP-replay (F1) — gate-agnostic, deferred; project criteria inherit it later.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `eval_solver.run_case` runs an arbitrary criterion prompt_id (built-in or project), not the\n      closed 3-id set; the invocation model is documented.\n- [ ] `rebar criteria eval <id>` runs must-fire/must-not-fire + discrimination fixtures live from\n      `.rebar/evals/` with N-run stability.\n- [ ] The calibration view prints recall, false-accept, Cohen's κ, agreement % per criterion, with\n      each metric defined; the eval `verdict` vocabulary is reconciled with the fixture `expect`.\n- [ ] FP-replay (F1) is explicitly out of scope.","id":"55b8-1eb4-2623-4616","parent_id":"3156-9092-1967-4367","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Per-criterion eval runner + calibration view (rebar criteria eval)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782872258493458001,"uuid":"17fbb267-10fb-4ee8-8491-3a9f043c103f"}